They have discovered that the sun operates on the same basic principles as other stars: It has been found that the activity of all stars in the system is driven by their luminosity, rotation, and nothing else.
To determine the Rossby number of a star, which is related to the plasma flow, both luminosity and rotation are considered together.
The smaller the Rossby number is, the less active the star is in terms of magnetic field reversals.
