The 802.11n standard operates on the frequencies 2.4 GHz and 5.0 GHz.
This allows it to be backwards compatible with 802.11a, 802.11b, and 802.11g, provided that the base station has dual radio.
The speed of 802.11n is significantly faster than that of its predecessors, which had a maximum theoretical throughput of 600 Mbit/s.
